The paper deals with deep learning and adversarial training, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of deep learning models to attacks, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes solutions to overfitting, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
